## Comparative Overview of Genomic Aligners used for Benchmarking of Renegene-GI

Renegene-GI is an in-house built scalabale genomic aligner which can accomodate both small and large genomes. 
Here in this project we have devised a pipeline to index, align and report the variants from clinically isolated microbial genomes extracted from various biological samples.
In this benchmarking study we used 30 state-or-the-art aligners against Renegene-GI to understand its scalabale potential and utility acorss this sample pool.

